Concatenating two UC_STRING values whose combined lengths would exceed
SIZE_MAX caused a size_t integer overflow in uc_vm_string_concat(),
previously returning NULL silently. NULL was then pushed onto the VM
stack with no exception raised, allowing execution to continue with a
corrupted result. The fix raises a Runtime error exception so the
condition is surfaced to script-level try/catch or terminates the script
with a readable error message.

Since reproducing the overflow requires strings near SIZE_MAX bytes
(infeasible in a test environment), the testcase below verifies that
exceptions raised within uc_vm_string_concat() propagate correctly
through the VM's arithmetic dispatch path.

-- Testcase --
{%
	let o = proto({}, {
		tostring: function() {
			die("string concat exception path check");
		}
	});

	try {
		let _ = "x" + o;
	}
	catch (e) {
		print(e.type, ": ", e.message, "\n");
	}
%}
-- End --

-- Expect stdout --
Error: string concat exception path check
-- End --
